<introContent>
	<!-- Link to Content on Overview Page -->
	<extensionContent id="common_ov_roles" name="Roles" alt-style="css/swt.properties" style="css/t-links.css" path="overview/@">
		<group style-id="content-group" id="content-group">
			<link style-id="content-link" label="Displaying only the tools you need" url="http://org.eclipse.ui.intro/showPage?id=common_roles_page"
			 id="common_ov_roles" alt="">
				<text>With capabilities, you see only the tools that fit your current role. You can hide tools that you don't use, 
				and the workbench will bring them back when you need them or ask for them.</text>
			</link>
		</group>
	</extensionContent>

	<!-- Actual Page -->
	<page style="$theme$/html/overview.css,../com.ibm.welcome.common.rational.doc/css/common.css" id="common_roles_page" style-id="page">
		<head src="brochure-head.html" />
		<title style-id="intro-header">$introTitle$</title> 
		<group id="container">
			<include path="overview/navigation-links"/>
			<!-- content -->
			<group id="page-content">
				<group id="content-header" label="Overview" filteredFrom="swt">
            		<text style-id="page-title" id="page-title" filteredFrom="html">Overview</text>
            	</group>
        
				<group id="brochure" style-id="brochure">
					<group style-id="brochure-content" id="brochure-content">
						<group style-id="contentpgTitle" filteredFrom="swt">
							<text>Roles and capabilities</text>
						</group>	
						<img style-id="right" src="images/capabilities-preferences.gif" alt="Setting the preferences for Capabilities" />
						<text id="paragraph1">
							The product user interface is composed of menus, toolbars, perspectives, views of information within the perspectives, 
							wizards, and contextual help. To reduce workspace clutter, a limited set of these tools is enabled by default
							when you start the product. To support this streamlining, all the product features are grouped into logical sets called
							roles and capabilities. 
						</text>
						<text id="paragraph2"><![CDATA[As you work, you can add more tools by activating additional roles, which enable additional product capabilities. 
							To find a list of capability options, click <b>Window</b> > <b>Preferences</b>,
							and then click <b>General</b> > <b>Capabilities</b>.]]></text>
						<text id="paragraph3"> 
							To enable tools by using the predefined roles, select the check boxes for the 
							capabilities you want. In many cases, there are dependencies between capabilities, so enabling or disabling a 
							capability automatically enables or disables other capabilities. </text>
						<group id="clear"><text></text></group>
						<img style-id="right" src="images/roles-welcome.gif" alt="Setting roles in the Welcome" />

